# Styling Guidelines

## CSS Variables System
Always use semantic CSS variables for theming:
- `--paper` - Main background color
- `--ink` - Primary text color
- `--ink-70` - Secondary text (70% opacity)
- `--ink-50` - Tertiary text (50% opacity)
- `--ink-20` - Subtle borders/accents (20% opacity)
- `--cyan` - Brand accent color
- `--cyan-20` - Cyan with 20% opacity
- `--deep` - Dark section backgrounds (not text color)
- `--code-bg` - Code block backgrounds

## Dark Mode Implementation
- Never use `bg-[var(--ink)]` for backgrounds - use `bg-[var(--deep)]` instead
- Text colors should use `--ink` variants for proper contrast
- Code blocks use `--code-bg` for consistent theming
- Theme state is managed in [src/App.jsx](mdc:src/App.jsx)

## Tailwind Usage
- Use arbitrary values for CSS variables: `text-[var(--ink)]`
- Prefer semantic variable names over hardcoded colors
- Use `Container` component from [src/utils/common.jsx](mdc:src/utils/common.jsx) for consistent spacing
- Apply `FadeIn` and `FadeInInitial` for animations

## Component Styling
- Use consistent border radius: `rounded-2xl` for cards, `rounded-3xl` for larger elements
- Apply hover states with `hover:` prefix
- Use `transition-colors` for smooth color changes
- Maintain consistent spacing with Tailwind's spacing scale